Biography

• 2023 AVCA First Team All-Southwest Region

• 2023 All-Big 12 Second Team

2023 (Junior)

Her first year with the Bears, her first as a DI athlete, starting at middle blocker … Played in all but one set of the season across 30 matches … Started in every match … Led the team in blocks 17 times … Led the team in aces on six occasions … Finished the season with 247 kills averaging 2.19 kills per set … Had a .368 hitting percentage for the year, tying for sixth in the Baylor record book with ’22 graduate Kara McGhee … Had nine matches with double-digit kills … Served up a pair of aces in three matches … Procured two aces against No. 17 Minnesota in the Big Ten/Big 12 Challenge (8/26) … Had a season-high seven-block match against No. 18 Rice, also her first 10-kill match (9/1) … In the upset of No. 19 Ohio State, she had a season-high hit percentage of .647 with 12 kills and one error, good for third in the BU record book for a five set match (9/15) … Had a then-season-high 14 kill performance against Kansas State (10/6) … Had two aces against Cincinnati on the road (10/13) … Served up three aces across the two matches with No. 5 Texas (10/26-27) … Upped her season-high to 16 kills against TCU (11/11) … Had 10 kills against James Madison in the first round of the NCAA Tournament (11/30) … Named Second Team All-Big 12 (11/28) … Named First Team AVCA All-Southwest Region (12/5).

MSUWP/High School:

She was the Region 16 Player of the Year and a First Team All-American in 2021 for Missouri State West Plains … Helped the Grizzlies to be Region 16 champions in both the Fall and Spring of 2021 with the Grizzlies finishing third in the Rankings for the Fall season … Played under coach Paula Wiedemann at MSUWP ... Played club with BVE under Junior Anomah in Cameroon ... Graduated high school from Lycee d'Etoug-Ebe.

Personal:

Full name is Ruth Manuela Marie Bibinbe ... Daughter of Ngo Yana Elisabeth and Elie Bibinbe ... Is one of six children in her family: Jeanne, Madeleine, Anne, Jean and Sabine ... Majoring in accounting ... Originally met Coach McGuyre through one of his former players, who is also from Cameroon, who was holding a camp in Houston.
